    <text id="B1188T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Carse reports that Johnson, the accused murderer, has been arrested. According to
                    newspaper reports, Johnson was arrested in Fishersville and initially held in
                    the Augusta County jail.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. and
                        A.L.</abbr><lb/>Sub District No 8 7th District <abbr expan="Virginia"
                            >Va</abbr><lb/>Rockbridge, Bath and Alleghany Counties
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Brigadier General">Bt Brig
                        Gen'l</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Adjutant General"
                        >A.A.G.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-10-15"><abbr expan="October">Oct</abbr> 15th 1866</date>
                        <name type="place"><abbr expan="Headquarters">HdQrs</abbr> Lexington <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>General</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to report that J. C. Johnson the man whom it is believed shot
                    Patrick Thompson (Freedman) on the night of Sunday the 7th inst has been
                    arrested and is now confined in the county jail -- awaiting trial.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Sir<lb/>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="obedient"
                        >obdt</abbr> Servant</salute>
                    <signed>G. B. Carse<lb/><abbr expan="Brevet">Bt</abbr> Colonel and<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst Supt</abbr> Bureau of <abbr
                            expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. and
                    A.L.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
